[[File:Brwm78.JPG|thumb|right|250px|A view of the [[Baranovichi]] railway museum]]

The first line crossing [[Belarus]] was the [[Saint Petersburg – Warsaw Railway]], which started operating in late 1862. This included section and railway station in Hrodna.<ref>http://www.rw.by/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=284&Itemid=57 Belarusian railway - Company - History</ref> During the mid 1860s, a railway line was also built from [[Daugavpils]] to [[Polatsk]] and further to [[Vitebsk]]. The [[Warsaw–Brest Railway]], opened in 1866, completed to [[Moscow]] in 1871.<ref>[http://www.sinfin.net/railways/world/belarus.html Some historical information about railways of Belarus]</ref>

