e --> | auxiliary_bishops = <!-- List most senior first (usually reckoned by date of consecration) --> | apostolic_admin = | vicar_general = | episcopal_vicar = | archdeacons = <!-- List most senior first (usually reckoned by date of first collation); use | archdeacon = for one--> | emeritus_bishops = Joseph Nguyên Van Yên <small>Bishop Emeritus (1998-2007)</small> <!---- Map ----> | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = [http://www.phatdiem.org/Portal/Default.aspx?Culture=vi-VN Website of the Diocese] | footnotes = }} The '''diocese of Phát Diệm''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis de Phat Diem|links=no}}) is a [[Roman Catholic]] diocese of [[Vietnam]]. The bishop position has been vacant since April 2007. However, on July 25, 2009, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] selected Rev. Joseph Nguyen Nang to head the diocese.
The creation of the diocese in present form was declared November 24, 1960.
The diocese covers an area of 1,787&nbsp;km², and is a [[suffragan diocese]] of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Hanoi|Archdiocese of Hanoi]].
By 2004, the diocese of Phát Diêm had about 144,721 believers (15.9% of the population), 31 [[priest]]s and 65 [[parish]]es.<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dphat.html Catholic Hierarchy Directory]</ref>
[[Image:16th century stone angel in Phat Diem cathedral.jpg|thumb|left|300px|19th century stone angel in Phát Diêm Cathedral]] [[Queen of the Rosary Cathedral]] in Kim Sơn ([[Ninh Bình Province]]) has been assigned as the [[Cathedral]] of the [[diocese]].<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/churches/data/cathVN.htm#chk GCatholic.org]</ref> This cathedral complex was built between 1875 and 1899 and comprises four churches and one basilica, as well as several parks, ponds and grottos.
