{{Infobox Union |name= CSdL |country= [[San Marino]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]], [[ETUC]] |members= 2400 |full_name= San Marino Confederation of Labour |native_name= Confederazione Sammarinese del Lavoro |image= [[Image:CSdL logo.png]] |founded= 1943 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Domagnano]], San Marino |people= [[Giovanni Ghiotti]], secretary general |website= [http://www.csdl.sm www.csdl.sm] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''San Marino Confederation of Labour''' (CSdL) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[San Marino]]. It was founded in 1943 and has a membership of 2400.
The CSdL is affiliated with the [[International Trade Union Confederation]], and the [[European Trade Union Confederation]].
